        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-12-16 07:37:08.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Patch Set 4:\n> \n> @Morgan, would you happen to know why ansible \"get_url\" is not storing helm3 as a tarball and instead is storing it as a text?\n> For now, this shell solution is ugly but unblocks Sylvain on one of the helm issues. \n> \n> Would you mind providing your review please?\n\nI gave a try on my lab\nit is working as expected\n\nok: [pod4.opnfv.fr]\n\nTASK [create directory] ******************************************************************************************************\nchanged: [pod4.opnfv.fr]\n\nTASK [Fetch tar.gz] ******************************************************************************************************\nchanged: [pod4.opnfv.fr]\n\nTASK [Unarchive] ******************************************************************************************************\nchanged: [pod4.opnfv.fr]\n\nPLAY RECAP ******************************************************************************************************pod4.opnfv.fr              : ok=4    changed=3    unreachable=0    failed=0    skipped=0    rescued=0    ignored=0   \n\nopnfv@pod4-jumphost0:/tmp/helm3$ ls\nhelm-v3.3.4-linux-amd64.tar.gz  linux-amd64\n\nthe ansible role looks fine on my side\nthe issue is probably linked to the target environment and/or jenkins integration\nyou shall retry with more verbosity to get more details",
        "patchset_number": 4
